				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">And personally I think its better with an AA than items, since it would be available for anyone. Ofcourse, everyone would have the same "boost" then, but perhaps that isn't that bad. And they can increase damage on melee etc by a percentage, so it would actually scale a bit anyway.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
If we only get power increases via AA then class balance compared to DPS melee will get worse. There is no other outcome when you get essentially 'free' upgrades that are available to everyone.
<br />

<br />
The current balance issues are totally dependent on the fact that casters are not dependent on gear enough and hence its impossible to achieve balance at both ends of the gear spectrum.
<br />

<br />
For example, going from bazaar/1groupable gear to Anguish gear then casters gain around 20% + a larger mana pool, melee gain > 50% in weapons alone and thats discounting effects such as Ferocity and Cleave (though they are obtained via bazaar or single groups nowadays though at a huge price)
<br />

<br />
Until the rate of gain of power with progression through the content is made more equal it will be impossible to balance DPS casters and melee at the 'bazaar' end of the spectrum and the 'Anguish' end of the spectrum.
<br />

<br />
The only solution in my opinion is to make casters either dependent on gear (which would require a massive overhaul to the current spells and the additions of far more extensive focus items) or change the way spells are obtained in that they become mob drops in much the same way weapons are. Basic spells would be as now but you'd getter better versions as drops.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=342751" target="_blank" class="postlink">Kirium</a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.cestusdei.org" target="_blank" class="postlink">Cestus Dei</a>
<br />
Veeshan</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
