				<td width="100%"><a href="viewtopic.php?p=285134&amp;sid=2c3bdbf4df42ac35fc70bbce5b46b6be#285134"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Thu Mar 10, 2005 12:52 pm<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
			        <td valign="top" align="right" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="ignore.php?mode=add&amp;username=Kirium_Veeshan&amp;topic=20423&amp;sid=2c3bdbf4df42ac35fc70bbce5b46b6be"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_ignore.gif" alt="Add User to Ignore List" title="Add User to Ignore List" border="0" /></a> <a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=285134&amp;sid=2c3bdbf4df42ac35fc70bbce5b46b6be"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>   </td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">The difference in gear going from a bazaar mage/1 groupable mage to an anguish mage is greater than 20%. And the mana pool difference is also > 50%
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Was curious as to just what the differences actually are (rather than base comments on just comparing foci effects, which does result in only a 20%'ish increase) I've performed a simple calculation to see just how much damage a 'bazaar' and 'anguish' geared mage would do if chain casting Bolt of Jerikor for various lengths of time.
<br />

<br />
Assumption made for these two hypothetical mages are as follows:
<br />

<br />
'Bazaar' Mage: 25% DD foci, 10% mana pres, 15% spell haste, 7000 Manapool, FT20.
<br />
'Anguish' Mage: 45% DD foci, 20% mana pres, 23% spell haste, 11000 manapool, FT20, click item from Tacvi, 9 mana regen from tacvi ear click and 3 mana regen from Shield of Dreams.
<br />

<br />
Each has access to identical buffs that yield mana regen and max buffed using rods (at 7 a tick, which is not strictly true after first rod unless have ele legs) gives the Bazaar mage Mana regen of 102 a tick and the Anguish mage 114 a tick.
<br />

<br />
Ok just how much damage can they do overtime assuming chain casting at fastest rate possible and getting average crits and no resists?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Code:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="code">
<br />
Time&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Bazaar&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Anguish&nbsp; &nbsp; %Gain
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 31356&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;37080&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 18.3
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;2&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 62712&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;74160&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 18.3
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;3&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 80006&nbsp; &nbsp; 111240&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 39.0
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;4&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 88118&nbsp; &nbsp; 145734&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 65.4
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;5&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 96230&nbsp; &nbsp; 156960&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 63.1
<br />
&nbsp; &nbsp;6&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;104342&nbsp; &nbsp; 168186&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 61.2
<br />
&nbsp; 10&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;136790&nbsp; &nbsp; 213090&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 55.8
<br />
&nbsp; 15&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;177350&nbsp; &nbsp; 269220&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 51.8
<br />
&nbsp; 20&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;217910&nbsp; &nbsp; 325350&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 49.3
<br />
&nbsp; 60&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;542390&nbsp; &nbsp; 758910&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 40.0</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
My estimate of 20% gain is clearly only applicable at the start of fights before the manapool runs out. Once the bazaar mages manapool runs out yet the Anguish mage is keeping going full bore the difference in percentage term rockets up until the point the Anguish mage aswell is oom and then running on regen.
<br />

<br />
The assumptions made on gear are pretty valid though 10% mana pres is low and 15% is available via summoned earring or even 15% PoP effects given the bolt is only Lvl 66. But that won't change things drastically.
<br />

<br />
Apart from the first few minutes then it does seem like there is consdierable scaling with gear. I've discounted any pet effects here (they are pretty minor) and the epic effects. Also AA's increase dps equally on both sides so that would actually narrow the gap in percentage terms.
<br />

<br />
How does this progression compare with melee? Then I expect melee gains with gear to be flat in percentage terms as they are not constrained by a manapool (endurance effects will be less). Also DPS enhancing melee discs are dependent on gear unlike mage dps enhancing aa's. 
<br />

<br />
