			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Strange. I'm an elemental flagged mage and I don't even have that much mana. Nor can I one group your range-slot aug unless I got a few Tacvi people.  Also, for the riftseeker gear - I'm assuming your "Bazaar mage" is running around with tanks and clerics that have slightly better gear. I don't think I've ever seen a tank in full ornate survive Balancer Relik. 
<br />

<br />
But, anyway.
<br />

<br />
My theory is we should not be a "nuking" class per se. We should have decent nukes, but a huge portion of our damage should come from pets. The recent water pet parse was a good exmaple of this - Pet and Mage were practically equal on a 1Million hp mob. 
<br />

<br />
I think we should be concentrated mainly on DPS, but we should have some utility that will set us apart in desireability vrs. Wizards, rogues, monks, rangers, etc. I think this, also, should come from pets.
<br />

<br />
My solution was to make pets be either extremely offensive, or extremely defensive. Pet focus scaling and availability needs to be re-examined, but we should have something besides that.
<br />

<br />
Frenzied burnout is an absolute joke. Make it something that is an honest, big increase in pet offense. Make another AA that wouldn't stack with it called "Elemental Defense" That gives your pet 40% more hp, proc Calliav and tank like a mofo. Or something. 
<br />

<br />
Whatever, The point is to make us useable through our pets. Do it through focus, AA, clicky items... doesn't really matter. We need to find a way to improve our pets, and I still feel its through being mutually exclusive. 
<br />

<br />
If my numbers are right, with Epic 2.0, Servant of Chaos, Pet Gear, Elemental Durability 3 (No buffs besides epic) Child of Earth is already over 11K tank - with buffs it pushes up near 14-15K. Theres a DAMN good reason that this pet has relativly low dps - It could replace a warrior in a group otherwise. 
<br />

<br />
Does anyone else think that high, but mutally exclusive increases, are a good idea? They allow us to form to a group - much like a druid. They can nuke or heal - or both. Now we can offtank with pets, or do huge dps - Or both. That is my ultimate goal, is to break us from our current "dps only" role without sacraficing dps, while getting much needed pet incerases.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
