			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">His comparison was valid.
<br />

<br />
Consider that there is some give and take at each level (baz and raid) as far as gear goes.  A simple look over at eqrankings shows a wide variety of stats for people in the same situation of gear attainability.
<br />

<br />
If youre going to compare to the top of the raid, you have to use the top of the baz.  Not all raid mages are in top end gear, just like not all baz mages would be.  So if youre going to assume a *player* has taken the time to amass a solid gearset, you have to assume that he will do so in either situation.
<br />

<br />
You can easily start with a lesser geared lower end and call it "average baz gear" but then you have to scale down the top to "average anguish gear" - and if you do that the percentages will follow a similar pattern:
<br />

<br />
Small change till lower mana pool runs out, big change till bigger mana pool runs out, less change as both are forced to med up midfight.  And that pattern (a parabola of relative percentages if graphed) does NOT comform to a melee graph which would be two linear lines one steeper than the other with the gap growing over time (small variances for dmg discs).<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=128142 " target="_blank" class="postlink">Lofwyr</a> - <a href="http://www.clubfu.net/" target="_blank" class="postlink">Club Fu</a> - Bristlebane</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
